<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 J 33/173a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-16T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                        1924—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>40. For your information. The Department today gave to the press the
                            following statement: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The American Minister to Rumania, Mr. Peter A. Jay, who has
                                    recently returned to this country from his post, was received by
                                    the President this morning. Mr. Jay later reported to the
                                    Secretary of State, with whom he consulted concerning American
                                    interests in Rumania.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>